<strong style="color: darkred;">Enrichment analysis</strong>  is a statistical procedure used to identify biological terms  which are over-represented in a given gene set. These include <strong style="color: darkred;">signaling pathways</strong> , <strong style="color: darkred;">molecular functions, diseases, and a wide variety of other biological terms</strong>  obtained by <strong style="color: darkred;">integrating prior knowledge</strong>  of gene function from multiple resources. 


<strong style="color: darkred;">Enrichr links</strong> : links to Enrichr containing the results of enrichment analyses generated by analyzing the <strong style="color: darkred;">up-regulated and down-regulated genes</strong>  from a differential expression analysis.By clicking on these links, users can interactively explore and download the enrichment results.
